Business Brief -- Pergament Home Centers Inc.:
   Lenders Will Gain Control
   In Restructuring Agreement
Robert Mancuso, who took the chain private in 1989, was
the majority shareholder. Mr. Mancuso, former president and
chief executive officer of Merrill Lynch Capital Partners,
said the four lenders, which weren't identified, received all
the equity in exchange for retiring $94.5 million in debt,
about half the company's total. Some of the lenders also
agreed to provide $40 million in working capital.
   The company also will fully repay trade creditors a total
of about $25 million over 10 months. Pergament said 1991
revenue was $360 million. Its stores are mainly on Long
Island.